.SH NAME
cert-ca-signed - Check whether a certificate is signed by a CA


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcert ca-signed [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Check whether a certificate is signed by a CA. The file pointed to by the
--ca is used as the CA certificate, and should contain only one CA
certificate.

.PP
Results will be output as one of:
+ SELF-SIGNED
+ INVALID
+ OK (expires )


